### Step 2 — `src/routes.ts` — replace the `GET /users` handler

```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page  = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page  as string) || 1);
  const limit = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.limit as string) || 10);

  const total      = users.length;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
  const startIndex = (page - 1) * limit;
  const data       = users.slice(startIndex, startIndex + limit);

  res.json({ data, pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages } });
});
```

**Why this works for all cases:**
- Missing/non-numeric params → `parseInt` returns `NaN`, `|| default` kicks in
- Out-of-range page (e.g. `?page=100`) → `startIndex` exceeds array length → `slice` returns `[]` naturally, no error needed
- `GET /users/:id` is completely untouched

